WorldStage Newsonline– Custodian Investment Plc, an investment holding company with significant interests in life and non-life insurance, pension fund has released its earnings forecast for the first quarter 2021 with profit after taxation projected to rise by 18.55% to N2.872 billion compared with N2.422 billion in Q1 2020. The company is also expecting its gross revenue to rise to N20.036 billion from N18.520 billion in Q1 2020. WorldStage earlier reported the company’s financial report for the period ended 30 September 2020 with 42% growth in gross revenue to N22.515 billion in Q3 2020 as against N15.855 billion in 2019.